you're here for 5 minutes

00:01:16.567 --> 00:01:18.033
and you want to do it.

00:01:18.033 --> 00:01:18.967
You want to be a commando.

00:01:18.967 --> 00:01:19.667
You want to play.

00:01:25.900 --> 00:01:28.066
BILLIE MINTZ: The most obvious
theme in all of Isaac's movies

00:01:28.066 --> 00:01:31.667
is brutal violence taken
to comedic extremes.

00:01:31.667 --> 00:01:35.133
[cheering]

00:01:35.133 --> 00:01:37.633
And that's exactly
the point, violence

00:01:37.633 --> 00:01:40.066
as an artistic expression,
Isaac believes,

00:01:40.066 --> 00:01:42.533
is not only his creative
passion but also

00:01:42.533 --> 00:01:43.934
his country's salvation.

00:01:57.500 --> 00:02:01.433
You want to clear the picture
of Ugandans killing people

00:02:01.433 --> 00:02:04.200
by making films of
Ugandans killing people?

00:02:08.800 --> 00:02:10.567
BILLIE MINTZ: Isaac's
over-the-top filmmaking style

00:02:10.567 --> 00:02:13.633
strikes a chord here, driving
modest movie ticket and DVD

00:02:13.633 --> 00:02:17.266
sales, which the actors are
also able to sell door to door,

00:02:17.266 --> 00:02:19.967
thereby supporting the
crew and their families.

00:02:19.967 --> 00:02:22.300
And Isaac isn't just
a local celebrity,

00:02:22.300 --> 00:02:24.867
he's an international
phenomenon with millions

00:02:24.867 --> 00:02:28.500
of hits on YouTube to confirm
his intensely devoted fan base.

00:02:28.500 --> 00:02:29.600
[singing]

00:02:37.800 --> 00:02:39.333
BILLIE MINTZ: Even more
devoted are the people

00:02:39.333 --> 00:02:41.533
who come from all
over Uganda to help

00:02:41.533 --> 00:02:46.266
create his micro low
budget full length films.

00:02:46.266 --> 00:02:50.266
[applause]

00:02:51.300 --> 00:02:53.500
Wow, guys, this
is so impressive.

00:02:53.500 --> 00:02:58.633
Any filmmaker in the world, no
matter how successful they are,

00:02:58.633 --> 00:03:01.667
would dream to have
a team like you guys.

